# Researcher — solo-law (build-prep)
Plan is locked. This file provides the exact scaffold commands, pinned libraries, seed data, worker code, i18n JSON, and design asset references the demo-builder needs to start without discovery.

---

## 1. Angular 18 Scaffold

```bash
# Run from upwork-runs/solo-law/
ng new solo-law-demo --style=css --routing=true --ssr=false --skip-git
cd solo-law-demo
```

Angular 18 generates standalone components by default (no NgModule needed). Base href is set at build time, not scaffold time.

**Build + copy to site:**
```bash
ng build --base-href /demos/solo-law/
cp -r dist/solo-law-demo/browser/* ../../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/solo-law/
```
(Create `public/demos/solo-law/` first if it doesn't exist.)

**angular.json — add these to `assets` array:**
```json
{ "glob": "**/*", "input": "src/assets", "output": "assets" },
{ "glob": "webllm-worker.js", "input": "src", "output": "/" }
```
This ensures `assets/i18n/*.json` and `webllm-worker.js` land at the site root.

---

## 2. Exact Library Installs (pinned)

```bash
# i18n
npm install @ngx-translate/core @ngx-translate/http-loader

# Tailwind
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p          # creates tailwind.config.js + postcss.config.js
```

No npm install for WebLLM — imported via CDN ESM in the worker only.

**versions confirmed compatible with Angular 18 + esbuild:**
- `@ngx-translate/core` >= 15.0 (Signal-native; `provideTranslateService` functional API)
- `@ngx-translate/http-loader` >= 8.0
- `tailwindcss` >= 3.4

**package.json scripts to add:**
```json
"build:demo": "ng build --base-href /demos/solo-law/ && cp -r dist/solo-law-demo/browser/* ../../../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/solo-law/"
```

