## 9. Seed Data — Publications (EN + ES)

```python
PUBLICATIONS = [
  {
    "slug": "force-majeure-supply-chain",
    "practice_area_slug": "corporate-transactions",
    "author": "Michael A. Wegter",
    "published_at": "2025-11-15",
    "en": {
      "title": "When the Deal Breaks: Force Majeure Clauses in an Era of Supply Chain Disruption",
      "excerpt": "Recent supply chain disruptions have tested contract terms that practitioners rarely invoked. This article examines how courts have interpreted force majeure provisions and offers drafting guidance for sophisticated commercial agreements.",
      "body_html": "<p>The commercial disruptions of recent years have elevated force majeure clauses from boilerplate to boardroom priority. Courts across jurisdictions have grappled with what constitutes a qualifying event, whether government-mandated shutdowns suffice, and how foreseeability doctrines apply to unprecedented disruption cascades.</p><p>This article surveys key judicial decisions, identifies the drafting failures that allowed disputes to arise, and proposes a framework for force majeure provisions that allocate risk with precision: explicit triggering events, notice mechanics, mitigation obligations, and termination rights structured to reflect the actual risk profile of the transaction.</p><p><strong>Key takeaways:</strong> Broad \"acts of God\" language provides less protection than practitioners assume. Specificity — naming disease outbreaks, regulatory actions, and logistics failures — matters. Economic hardship alone does not excuse performance in most jurisdictions without an explicit provision.</p>"
    },
    "es": {
      "title": "Cuando el acuerdo se rompe: cláusulas de fuerza mayor en la era de la disrupción de cadenas de suministro",
      "excerpt": "Las recientes disrupciones en las cadenas de suministro han puesto a prueba cláusulas contractuales que los profesionales rara vez invocaban. Este artículo examina cómo los tribunales han interpretado las disposiciones de fuerza mayor y ofrece orientación de redacción para acuerdos comerciales sofisticados.",
