- produced: researcher.out — full build-prep package: Angular 18 scaffold command, Tailwind config + CSS vars + Google Fonts URL, ngx-translate app.config.ts pattern, webllm-worker.js exact code + agentic loop skeleton, all routes, i18n JSON (EN/ES/FR), complete bilingual seed data (4 practice areas + 5 publications), Flask OOP blueprint skeleton, server.py registration pointer, Playwright config stub, Unsplash image URLs
- decisions: Angular route lazy-loads all pages; worker ESM from esm.run CDN; seed cred = `editor@solo-law.demo` / `Demo2026!`; no ngx-translate version pinned (use latest `>=15.0`); hero uses CSS gradient + Unsplash URLs (no bundled images); JetBrains Mono limited to CMS internal UI per plan
- next_needs: demo-builder runs `ng new solo-law-demo ...`, installs libs, drops the files above, builds Flask OOP blueprint with full CRUD from this seed data, pushes mw-backend, verifies `/solo-law/health` live; priority order per CEO = public editorial site first, then CMS CRUD, then AI panel
- risks: Angular esbuild builder (default in v18) + Tailwind requires `postcss.config.js` from `npx tailwindcss init -p` — if missing, Tailwind classes silently generate no CSS; `webllm-worker.js` must be listed in `angular.json` assets or it 404s; Unsplash CDN URLs may be rate-limited in CI — preload them or use local stubs if deploy-test fails on image load
